11:01.163 --> 11:03.128
But how to make it look
like an accident?

11:03.129 --> 11:04.196
I'm not saying murder.

11:04.197 --> 11:05.912
Just talk to her
like a normal person.

11:05.998 --> 11:07.432
Right, even better,

11:07.433 --> 11:09.000
get her to tell me
all her little secrets

11:09.001 --> 11:12.293
then if she tries anything...
Uhh... we can destroy her.

11:20.974 --> 11:22.013
Hello, Peralta.

11:22.014 --> 11:23.515
Oh, my God! Hi.

11:23.516 --> 11:24.616
What's going on here?

11:24.617 --> 11:27.586
Funny story.
I took these files home

11:27.587 --> 11:29.688
a while ago,
even though I shouldn't have.

11:29.689 --> 11:31.923
And now,
I'm bringing them back.

11:31.924 --> 11:33.191
Isn't that funny?

11:33.192 --> 11:35.627
Are you laughing
behind the mask?

11:35.628 --> 11:37.151
No.

11:41.759 --> 11:42.759
Kev!

11:42.760 --> 11:43.826
Jake, it's after midnight.

11:43.827 --> 11:45.428
This had better be
about a murder.

11:45.429 --> 11:46.496
No, I wish.

11:46.497 --> 11:47.664
Look, I'm really sorry,

11:47.665 --> 11:49.163
but I have to talk
to captain Holt.

11:49.169 --> 11:51.067
Raymond,
your work life is here.

11:51.068 --> 11:53.069
Please, come in.
Take off your shoes.

11:53.070 --> 11:54.544
Neither of us want that.

11:56.507 --> 11:58.214
What is going on,
Peralta?

11:58.220 --> 11:59.976
This has been
a long day.

11:59.977 --> 12:02.779
Well, I.A.B. caught me
returning some classified files,

12:02.780 --> 12:04.380
and I am now
the prime suspect

12:04.381 --> 12:06.549
in the mole investigation,
and Miller said I would be

12:06.550 --> 12:07.784
suspended in the morning.

12:07.785 --> 12:10.520
But more importantly,
what does the "J" stand for?

12:10.521 --> 12:12.088
James?
John?

12:12.089 --> 12:13.523
Jo-Jo?

12:13.524 --> 12:14.791
My middle name
is more important to you

12:14.792 --> 12:16.025
than being suspended?

12:16.026 --> 12:17.608
If it's Jo-Jo? Yes.

12:17.614 --> 12:20.330
Look, I came here because we
have to figure this thing out.

12:20.331 --> 12:22.398
Miller is sure there's a mole
in the precinct,

12:22.399 --> 12:24.000
and the only way
to prove it's not me

12:24.001 --> 12:25.268
is to figure out
who it is.

12:25.269 --> 12:26.636
You said there was no mole.

12:26.637 --> 12:28.538
You said you knew everything
about these people.

12:28.539 --> 12:30.640
Well, it turns out
I don't.

12:30.641 --> 12:32.842
I've learned some truly
horrible things tonight.

12:32.843 --> 12:34.611
You were right,
and I was wrong.

12:34.612 --> 12:35.845
Goodness.

12:35.846 --> 12:37.180
Boyle is sleeping
with Gina?

12:37.181 --> 12:39.482
What? How could you
possibly know that?

12:39.483 --> 12:41.150
"You were right
and I was wrong."

12:41.151 --> 12:42.685
You must have been
shaken to your core

12:42.686 --> 12:43.720
to say that to me.

12:43.721 --> 12:45.121
Boyle is your
most trusted friend,

12:45.122 --> 12:46.189
so he has to be involved.

12:46.190 --> 12:47.790
Your use
of the word "horrible"

12:47.791 --> 12:50.126
leads me to believe that
the matter was sexual in nature,

12:50.127 --> 12:52.095
given your obvious immaturity.

12:52.096 --> 12:53.496
Pfft. I've had sex.

12:53.497 --> 12:55.131
And, of course,
you would be most upset

12:55.132 --> 12:56.833
if Boyle were to have
slept with someone

12:56.834 --> 12:58.034
you knew
from your childhood.

12:58.035 --> 13:01.738
Thus, the solve:
Gina and Charles.

13:01.739 --> 13:03.196
That was amazing.

13:03.202 --> 13:04.707
Come into my study.

13:04.708 --> 13:06.643
Let's figure out
who that mole is.

13:06.644 --> 13:08.878
I took all the giggle I had.

13:08.879 --> 13:10.780
There might be
some left in my mouth

13:10.781 --> 13:12.015
if you wanna make out.

13:12.016 --> 13:13.383
That sounds amazing.

13:13.384 --> 13:15.652
I'd love to make out
with you once I'm super high.

13:15.653 --> 13:17.287
Where can I get some?

13:17.288 --> 13:18.961
That girl over there
sold it to me.

13:19.490 --> 13:20.857
(Terry)
What happened, Ava?

13:20.858 --> 13:23.059
I thought you said
you didn't drink or do drugs.

13:23.060 --> 13:24.627
I don't.
Do you know how much math

13:24.628 --> 13:26.195
is involved
in dealing drugs?

13:26.196 --> 13:27.530
You gotta keep
a clear head.

13:27.531 --> 13:29.232
Look, this doesn't have
to be a big deal.

13:29.233 --> 13:31.034
Just give us the name
of your supplier.

13:31.035 --> 13:32.568
How'd you get involved in
dealing giggle?

13:32.569 --> 13:35.238
Wait, wait, wait, wait.
We gotta back this up.

13:35.239 --> 13:36.839
After pre-school,
did you go to private

13:36.840 --> 13:38.441
or public elementary?

13:38.442 --> 13:39.642
Private.

13:39.643 --> 13:41.844
When were you potty-trained?
That's so random.

13:41.845 --> 13:43.528
Sarge,
the giggle pig.

13:43.534 --> 13:45.715
All right, let's go
through the squad one by one.

13:45.716 --> 13:47.050
Rosa's very secretive.

13:47.051 --> 13:49.185
I don't know anything
about her personal life.

13:49.186 --> 13:51.327
Charles has expensive tastes.

13:51.333 --> 13:53.823
Gina has said many times
that she would sell us all out

13:53.824 --> 13:55.491
for five minutes
with Blake Griffin.

13:55.492 --> 13:58.127
Let's see, Terry wants to send
his twins to private school.

13:58.128 --> 14:00.096
But on his salary,
that's difficult.

14:00.097 --> 14:01.631
Mm...
Plus with twins,

14:01.632 --> 14:04.867
one of them's always evil,
so...

14:04.868 --> 14:05.967
It's Cagney.

14:07.057 --> 14:09.439
Gina, is everything okay?

14:09.440 --> 14:10.673
You never text me.

14:10.674 --> 14:11.941
Look,
the last message I got

14:11.942 --> 14:13.509
from you was
august 3rd, 2009.

14:13.510 --> 14:15.578
You wrote, "sup, Rosa?"

14:15.579 --> 14:17.228
Followed by, "never mind."

14:17.234 --> 14:19.115
It's over between
me and Charles.

14:19.116 --> 14:20.439
I'm so upset.

14:20.445 --> 14:24.020
Amy, when will I ever find
a relationship as perfect

14:24.021 --> 14:25.822
as the one you have
with Freddy?

14:25.823 --> 14:27.924
It's Teddy,
and it's not perfect.

14:27.925 --> 14:29.392
Believe me.

14:29.393 --> 14:30.693
All his underwear
are lined with mesh

14:30.694 --> 14:32.428
like a bathing suit.
Is it medical?

14:32.429 --> 14:34.161
How do you even
ask that?

14:34.167 --> 14:36.289
I don't know,
but keep talking.

14:36.295 --> 14:39.000
(Jake) What else, what else,
what else?

14:39.006 --> 14:41.137
[Snaps]
Wait a minute.

14:41.138 --> 14:43.462
One time, I saw Rosa
eating watermelon.

14:43.468 --> 14:45.341
But then,
when I asked her about it,

14:45.342 --> 14:48.811
she said she'd never eaten
that or any other kind of melon.

14:48.812 --> 14:50.847
Now that I say it out loud,
it doesn't seem like much.

14:50.848 --> 14:52.248
No.
Put it on the board!

14:52.249 --> 14:53.583
Oh!

14:53.584 --> 14:55.852
<i>Hey, check it out.</i>

14:55.853 --> 14:58.521
Dog bra.
[Dog growling]

14:58.522 --> 15:01.024
Dog bra.

15:01.025 --> 15:03.927
Oh, I'm so tired.
I can't keep my eyes open.

15:03.928 --> 15:06.195
Here...
I need you to slap me.

15:06.196 --> 15:08.031
I'm not gonna do that,
Peralta.

15:09.867 --> 15:11.568
Oh!
I thought perhaps

15:11.569 --> 15:13.369
the element
of surprise would help.

15:13.370 --> 15:14.837
It did!

15:14.838 --> 15:17.774
I can't believe we can't
figure out who the mole is.

15:17.775 --> 15:20.810
Well, there is someone
we haven't talked about yet.

15:20.811 --> 15:22.378
Detective Jake Peralta.

15:22.379 --> 15:24.047
What?

15:24.048 --> 15:26.616
Someone's got a case
of the sleepover jokies.

15:26.617 --> 15:27.884
Why would I be
the mole?

15:27.885 --> 15:30.353
You were just caught
sneaking classified material

15:30.354 --> 15:31.321
into the precinct.

15:31.322 --> 15:34.221
You spent six months
undercover in the mafia

15:34.227 --> 15:36.259
and have many
criminal contacts.

15:36.260 --> 15:37.794
You've been known
to flaunt departmental rules

15:37.795 --> 15:40.937
and regulations,
and you are deeply in debt.

15:40.943 --> 15:45.368
Well, if you hadn't tricked me
into getting car insurance,

15:45.369 --> 15:46.903
I wouldn't be in debt.

15:46.904 --> 15:49.639
You wanna do me?
I'll do you right back.

15:49.640 --> 15:51.040
Tit for toot.

15:51.041 --> 15:52.609
I've been on the force
for 30 years,

15:52.610 --> 15:54.344
and I've never been accused
of impropriety.

15:54.345 --> 15:55.778
Oh, is that a fact?

15:55.779 --> 15:57.547
Because I heard you call
deputy chief Wuntch

15:57.548 --> 15:59.382
by her first name
and after that,

15:59.383 --> 16:01.284
you told her you hoped
she got carried off by crows.

16:01.285 --> 16:02.785
That is gross
insubordination.

16:02.786 --> 16:04.754
Madeline is irrelevant.

16:04.755 --> 16:06.322
Our battles extend
beyond the confines

16:06.323 --> 16:08.458
of NYPD rules.

16:08.459 --> 16:09.626
You're being ridiculous.

16:09.627 --> 16:11.194
Am I? If you're
such a great cop,

16:11.195 --> 16:12.695
how come you didn't know
there was a mole

16:12.696 --> 16:13.696
in your precinct?

16:13.697 --> 16:14.964
That's right...
Because you did.

16:14.965 --> 16:16.399
Because you are the mole,
you mole!

16:16.400 --> 16:17.700
I've heard enough!

16:17.701 --> 16:19.836
Please return
your guest pajamas,

16:19.837 --> 16:21.371
guest toothbrush,
and guest slippers,

16:21.372 --> 16:23.573
and get out of here.

16:23.574 --> 16:25.982
It's time for you
to be suspended.

16:29.998 --> 16:31.732
Peralta, shouldn't you be
suspended by now?

16:31.733 --> 16:33.834
Yes, and I know that you're mad
that I'm here,

16:33.835 --> 16:35.402
but you're about to
get over it,

16:35.403 --> 16:37.137
because I know
who the mole is.

16:37.138 --> 16:38.572
Lieutenant Miller.

16:38.573 --> 16:40.674
I don't think
he's with I.A.B. at all.

16:40.675 --> 16:42.376
I think he's spying
for Wuntch.

16:42.377 --> 16:44.177
Wuntch?
You said it yourself.

16:44.178 --> 16:45.746
Your battles extend
beyond the confines

16:45.747 --> 16:47.180
of NYPD rules.

16:47.181 --> 16:48.749
She wants information
about your task force,

16:48.750 --> 16:52.119
but she can't get access,
so she sent in a spy.

16:52.120 --> 16:53.654
That's why Miller
was skulking around

16:53.655 --> 16:56.323
the file room when I was
supposed to be the only skulker.

16:56.324 --> 16:58.325
That's interesting.
I did notice something odd

16:58.326 --> 17:00.494
when he and Wuntch first met.
She just nodded at him.

17:00.495 --> 17:02.560
She didn't even try
to shake his hand.

17:05.733 --> 17:08.669
She already knew
he was a germaphobe

17:08.670 --> 17:09.935
because they'd met before.

17:09.936 --> 17:11.171
Yes.

17:11.172 --> 17:13.173
Unfortunately,
we don't have any hard proof

17:13.174 --> 17:14.540
that they're working
together.

17:14.541 --> 17:19.579
Well, lucky for you,
proof is my middle name.

17:19.579 --> 17:21.915
And yours is Jared.

17:21.915 --> 17:22.915
Juice box.

17:22.916 --> 17:23.950
Jellyfish.

17:23.951 --> 17:25.915
[Gasps]
Jamiroquai!

17:28.189 --> 17:29.856
Lieutenant Miller.

17:29.857 --> 17:31.091
What do you want,
Peralta?

17:31.092 --> 17:32.381
I wanna play ball.

17:32.387 --> 17:34.394
Clear my name,
and I'll give you information

17:34.395 --> 17:35.662
about captain Holt.

17:35.663 --> 17:38.095
Well, I'm interested.
What kind of information?

17:38.633 --> 17:40.634
It's all on this.

17:40.635 --> 17:41.968
Pretty dope drive, right?

17:41.969 --> 17:43.937
It's a USB
shaped like a gun.

17:43.938 --> 17:45.238
Boink!

17:47.442 --> 17:48.976
All right,
I'll give it to my superiors

17:48.977 --> 17:50.477
and I'll be in contact.

17:50.478 --> 17:52.943
Hey, I know you only wanted
to hang out last night

17:53.448 --> 17:54.748
so you could find out
dirt on me.

17:54.749 --> 17:56.655
What?
Uh-uh.

17:56.661 --> 18:00.242
Look, you don't
have to be worried.

18:00.248 --> 18:03.123
I'll never tell anyone
about you and Charles.

18:03.124 --> 18:05.792
But honestly, it's not
as embarrassing as you think.

18:05.793 --> 18:10.697
It was shocking, but then I got
over it, and it seemed normal.

18:10.698 --> 18:13.867
Except for seeing how hairless
Charles' legs are.

18:13.868 --> 18:15.469
I mean, does he shave them?

18:15.470 --> 18:17.170
No, he wears
really cheap pants

18:17.171 --> 18:20.273
and as far as I can tell,
he's been chafed smooth.

18:20.274 --> 18:21.274
Yikes.

18:21.275 --> 18:22.576
Imagine that
wrapped around you.

18:22.577 --> 18:23.577
Okay.

18:25.513 --> 18:27.414
Okay. I could get in a lot
of trouble for this.

18:27.415 --> 18:31.018
But the big secret
about captain Holt is...

18:31.019 --> 18:34.354
That I have a flair
for the dramatic.

18:34.355 --> 18:35.945
Look behind you,
Madeline.

18:37.992 --> 18:40.761
<i>[Holt clearing throat]
(Jake) We're actually in front of you.</i>

18:40.762 --> 18:43.030
That's my fault... I thought the
layout was gonna be different.

18:43.031 --> 18:44.031
I didn't know how you guys
were gonna be sitting.

18:44.032 --> 18:45.065
I took a chance.

18:45.066 --> 18:46.500
Miller may be
in internal affairs,

18:46.501 --> 18:48.368
but he wasn't here
on official business.

18:48.369 --> 18:50.137
You sent him
to spy on us.

18:50.138 --> 18:52.706
That's a flagrant
ethics violation, Madeline.

18:52.707 --> 18:54.207
And it could sink you.

18:54.208 --> 18:56.590
Fine, you're right.
But you can't prove that.

18:56.676 --> 18:58.612
It's just your word
against mine.

18:58.613 --> 19:02.449
Ooh, actually,
it's your word against you.

19:02.450 --> 19:03.684
Pardon me.

19:03.685 --> 19:06.186
I put a recording device
in this dope drive,

19:06.187 --> 19:08.221
so I got your whole
conversation.

19:08.222 --> 19:09.389
(Holt)
You're going to leave

19:09.390 --> 19:10.957
my precinct
and my task force alone.

19:10.958 --> 19:12.325
Or else...

19:12.326 --> 19:14.061
You're...

19:14.062 --> 19:16.396
Wuntch meat.

19:16.397 --> 19:17.931
You sure you wanna go
with that one?

19:17.932 --> 19:18.999
Absolutely.
It's hilarious.

19:19.000 --> 19:20.233
All right.

19:20.234 --> 19:21.268
Hey.

19:21.269 --> 19:22.969
I'm sorry
about last night.

19:22.970 --> 19:25.005
I let my personal stuff
affect the job.

19:25.006 --> 19:26.006
It's okay.

19:26.007 --> 19:27.074
No, it's not.

19:27.075 --> 19:29.276
This morning,
I did some real police work.

19:29.277 --> 19:30.877
I called
the learning grove.

19:30.878 --> 19:32.612
They never had an
"Ava Watson,"

19:32.613 --> 19:34.114
so I faxed
them a picture.

19:34.115 --> 19:36.717
They identified her
as Rebecca Lubbock.

19:36.718 --> 19:39.386
I pulled her phone records
and...

19:39.387 --> 19:41.922
I think we have some good leads
on a possible supplier.

19:41.923 --> 19:43.512
Wow, nice work.

19:43.598 --> 19:45.125
And hey,
you should never worry

19:45.126 --> 19:46.393
about your kids.

19:46.394 --> 19:48.228
You're the best dad
I know.

19:48.229 --> 19:49.796
Cagney and Lacey
are gonna grow up great.

19:49.797 --> 19:51.531
You think so?
100%.

19:51.532 --> 19:52.899
You're right.

19:52.900 --> 19:54.735
They're gonna be
twin presidents.

19:54.736 --> 19:56.036
They'll either run
as one person

19:56.037 --> 19:58.027
and trick everyone,
or they'll as two

19:58.033 --> 20:01.007
and serve for
16 consecutive years.

20:01.008 --> 20:03.449
It's a damned Dynasty.

20:03.455 --> 20:05.245
Excuse me,
I have an announcement to make.

20:05.246 --> 20:07.948
Can I have everyone's attention,
please.

20:07.949 --> 20:09.955
Charles Boyle and I
had sex.

20:09.961 --> 20:11.318
What the hell?

20:11.319 --> 20:13.042
Gina,
what are you doing?

20:13.048 --> 20:14.121
Amy was right.

20:14.122 --> 20:15.222
People will be shocked,
and then they'll get over it

20:15.223 --> 20:16.754
and we can move on.

20:16.760 --> 20:19.393
At least this way, I get
to control how it gets out.

20:19.394 --> 20:21.528
I'm about to Olivia pope
this sitch.

20:21.529 --> 20:23.096
First off, I would like
to remind you all

20:23.097 --> 20:25.932
about several notable men
from my past.

20:25.933 --> 20:27.473
The rock-climbing backpacker,

20:27.479 --> 20:28.902
<i>the underwear model,</i>

20:28.903 --> 20:30.837
the guy who looked like
Tywin Lannister.

20:30.838 --> 20:31.905
<i>I bring these men
to mind</i>

20:31.906 --> 20:33.707
so you can appreciate
this dalliance

20:33.708 --> 20:36.076
for what it was...
An outlier.

20:36.077 --> 20:37.577
I will now
take questions.

20:37.578 --> 20:38.779
How was the sex?

20:38.780 --> 20:39.846
Gross.

20:39.847 --> 20:41.314
The sex was gross,
or I'm gross?

20:41.315 --> 20:43.316
You're gross.
The sex was adequate.

20:43.317 --> 20:44.718
How many times
did you do it?

20:44.719 --> 20:45.852
16 and 1/3.

20:45.853 --> 20:47.487
Don't ask, can't explain.

20:47.488 --> 20:49.322
I have a question.

20:49.323 --> 20:51.558
Do you have
any regrets?

20:51.559 --> 20:53.999
No.
It was pretty fun.

20:55.830 --> 20:57.297
[Mouths word]

20:57.298 --> 20:59.255
Thank you so much
for coming out today.

20:59.261 --> 21:01.601
Hey, I should've said this
last night,

21:01.602 --> 21:04.571
but your first casual
relationship... nice work!

21:04.572 --> 21:05.806
I know!

21:05.807 --> 21:07.541
I didn't even propose
to her once.

21:07.542 --> 21:09.643
Jake, I'm so sorry
I lied to you.

21:09.644 --> 21:10.911
I mean, I wanted
to tell you so badly.

21:10.912 --> 21:12.846
But I promised Gina
I wouldn't tell anyone.

21:12.847 --> 21:14.381
You kept a promise
to a friend.

21:14.382 --> 21:16.283
That sounds like
the Charles I know.

21:16.284 --> 21:18.952
Just like I know
everyone here.

21:18.953 --> 21:21.321
Yes, you do.
Although, there is something

21:21.322 --> 21:23.723
you didn't know about me.

21:23.724 --> 21:25.792
My middle name...

21:25.793 --> 21:27.961
Is Jacob.

21:27.962 --> 21:29.830
What?

